<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Saturday, Sept. 25. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
ENDORSE _ In a maneuver unusual even for the aerial dogfighting of
Arizona politics, former combat pilot Sen. John McCain announced
Friday that Arizona Gov. Jane Hull had endorsed a rival, Texas Gov.
George W. Bush, for the presidency. Hull's office, clearly taken by
surprise, denied that the governor had endorsed Bush. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
