<P>
   SAFRICA-ARMY-INTEGRATION (Bloemfontein, South Africa) _ Last
week, as weeping families buried their dead and government
officials promised a thorough inquiry, the nation embarked on a
soul-wrenching debate over the the racial transformation of the
National Defense Force. Since 1994, more than 22,700 former
liberation fighters and black homeland soldiers have been
integrated into the military, Government statistics show. The
Defense Force, which was then 45 percent white and 38 percent
black, is now less than 31 percent white and more than 55 percent
black. By Rachel L. Swarns.
