<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sept. 26 and thereafter. For questions about stories, please
contact Elizabeth Slocum at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   LA-DONUTS (Los Angeles) _ Long live the king. Newcomer Krispy
Kreme took on the reigning donut monarchs in L.A.'s San Fernando
Valley _ Foster's, Winchell's, Earl's, Yum Yum and Blinky's _ and
ran circles around them. A blue-ribbon panel of experts _ Daily
News Food editor Natalie Haughton, food critic Larry Lipson,
business writer Gregory J. Wilcox and two deputy sheriffs _ judged
a box full glazed doughnuts from each establishment. Krispy Kreme
ate up the competition.
</P>
<P>
   By Steve Carney. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
