<HEADLINE>
COMMENTARY: ISN'T THAT INTERESTING 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 By MAUREEN DOWD    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Pat Buchanan calls Ross Perot to tell him he is bolting from the
Republican Party and going for the Reform Party nomination:
</P>
<P>
   BUCHANAN: Ross, my friend, the Buchanan brigades are going to
charge up your hill. Mount up, everybody! Grab your pitchforks! I
am not going to let that little girl, Katie Couric, and all those
simpering liberals and the Israeli lobby and blood-sucking
Manhattan Money People like Rubin and Goldman and Sachs intimidate
me. Pat Buchanan is not an anti-Semite. For heaven's sake, some of
my best co-hosts are Jewish folks. I've done 2,000 ``Crossfires''
with Michael Kinsley!
</P>
<P>
   Pat Buchanan is not a hater or a bigot. But, Ross, as of 1939,
World War II WAS avoidable. Hitler was a man of great intuition and
courage, a soldier's soldier. If we had just ignored Adolf, he was
going East, not West. Poland was a goner anyway. And do we really
care if all those godless Communists in Russia ended up eating
Wiener schnitzel and driving Volkswagens? Plus, we'd have been
spared those sappy Normandy and Auschwitz movies by Spielberg and
the Hollywood Amen Corner.
</P>
<P>
   PEROT: Well, isn't that interesting. Let's see if the dogs eat
the dog food. If I came to you today, my friend, and said I have a
brand new screwdriver I'd like you to invest in, how can you be
sure the plastic handle won't break off the shaft? Did you know
that the Vietnamese in 1969 sent a team of five Black Panthers to
kill me? My dog chased them off faster than a Domino's pizza.
</P>
<P>
   But this is not about me. This is about our country. It's time
to take out the trash and clean out the stable. I used to think you
were a belligerent loudmouth, Pat Buchanan, jawing about building a
wall between us and ``Jose.'' I said to myself, ``This is some
beltway TV sissy that probably has trouble buying cat food, he's so
inexperienced.''
</P>
<P>
   I mean, it was sad, you and that look-alike sister of yours
running around pretending you had a campaign when you were just
chewing on the other candidates' cat or rabbit. But then I did some
background and credit checks on you, and I learned we have a lot in
common. We both love acting militaristically, but we were too
delicate for the military. You got out of Vietnam with a bad knee
even though you jog, and I pulled strings to try for an early
discharge from the Navy because the promiscuity and drinking upset
me.
</P>
<P>
   We are both lovable populist demagogues who want to revive a
Norman Rockwell world. We live by paranoia, paternalism,
protectionism, taking votes away from Bush fellas, and outflanking
Jesse Ventura. People say the only thing I should run for is the
insane asylum. But Jesse's the nutcake, the crazy aunt in fringe
and boas you keep down in the basement. Does he think I'd let a
wrestler who has gone to bawdy houses steal my party that I paid
for with my own money? If I live to be as old as Noah _ and he was
400 when the flood came _ I'll never let that happen.
</P>
<P>
   BUCHANAN: Ross, my friend, we must put America First. We must
honor our boys in the battlefields of Cold Harbor, Antietam and
Gettysburg, and save this once-Christian country that has been
force-fed the poisons of paganism. We must stop the Bush
conspiracy, the reign of Skull &AMP; Bones International, the One
World-New World Order-Wall Street-Trilateral Commission cabal of
Communists, financiers and plutocrats. W. is the bellhop of the
Council on Foreign Relations.
</P>
<P>
   PEROT: Isn't that interesting. Did you know that the Bushes
plotted with the Bilderbergers to disrupt my daughter's wedding?
Did you know a secret team of ex-military men and CIA officials is
seeking control of the government?
</P>
<P>
   BUCHANAN: That Lenora Fulani is a nice lady. I hope she doesn't
bellyache just because I love the Confederate flag and ``Dixie'' a
heck of a lot more than I care for bongo drums.
</P>
<P>
   PEROT: Now, isn't that interesting. Jesse's pushing Donald
Trump. Trump says he's the most popular guest on Larry King. But
Larry will tell you that there's only one world-class guest who
jams the CNN switchboards _ yours truly. Joe Friday, just the
facts, ma'am. Let me say flat out: Trump is in this for himself. An
eccentric, egotistical billionaire who wants to get more attention
by running for president. That is just sad. God help the U.S.A.
</P>
<P>
   Did you know that 59 percent of the people with flying saucer
experiences voted for me for president?
</P>
<P>
   BUCHANAN: Isn't that interesting.
</P>
</TEXT>
