   DEMS _ WASHINGTON _ Vice President Al Gore shed his trademark
formality in an unusually emotional speech that energized powerful
Democrats on Saturday, the strongest indication yet that Gore
understands the formidable challenge he faces from Bill Bradley for
the party's 2000 presidential nomination. (Shepard, Cox News
Service) MOVED
</P>
