captured in Africa and forced to cross the Atlantic Ocean to the
Americas, where they became slaves. More than 1,000 black
descendants of those slaves were led by the Rev. Johnny Ray
Youngblood, of the St. Paul Community Baptist Church in Brooklyn,
to the sunrise service. The service was part of a weeklong
observance of the heritage of slavery in many black churches across
