fetus is partially extracted from the womb and then killed by the
insertion of a tube into the skull and the extraction of the brain.
The ruling represents the first significant legal step that may
compel the Supreme Court to determine the constitutionality of laws
barring the procedure. (G. Paul Burnett/New York Times Photo)
