Department lacks the skilled people it needs to deal with the
post-cold-war era. The lofty ideal of the United States' leadership
and spreading the message of democracy and free markets cannot be
accomplished, she says, when ``we cannot staff our embassies, let
alone the department.'' (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
</P>
