<P>
   &QL; 
PILOTS-F16 _ Luke Air Force Base is under the gun to churn out more
fighter pilots at the very time when its aging fleet of F-16s is
shrinking and under duress. The base, the world's largest for F-16
training, is boosting class sizes to offset one of the worst Air
Force pilot shortages ever. In the past four years, Luke's
basic-training class increased by nearly a third, from 113 pilots
to 168. By JENNIFER BARRETT. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
ARENA _ The advertising agent for America West Arena earned at
least $5.2 million in commissions from 1992 to 1998, or about
three-quarters of a million more than Phoenix, which owns the
arena, received for the same period, city records show. What's
more, the agent, Terry Pugh of Paradise Valley, and Suns President
Jerry Colangelo formed a side deal, in violation of the arena
advertising agreement, that lasted for 28 months. By NENA BAKER.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
PARKING _ As vehicles continue to expand _ Ford's newest, the
Excursion, could be used as a small bus _ and parking spots have
shrunk to compact sizes (more cars per row equal more shoppers in
the store), the battle between the SUV and the car has developed
into its own asphalt class warfare in metro Phoenix parking lots.
By LAURA TRUJILLO. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
TV-GOODY (Undated) _ The story of how David E. Kelley named the
private detective agency in his new show, Snoops, tells you
something about how his mind works. Unfortunately, that story is
more interesting than the show itself. By BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story
will move in the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN _ (Phoenix) They're the Osmond Brothers of the
National League. In the rock and roll world of professional sports,
they're Lawrence Welk. If the Arizona Diamondbacks were a
television show, it'd be Father Knows Best. If they were a book,
it'd be the Boy Scout manual. I'm wondering, Why? Guys in the real
world not only tolerate a little bad behavior from professional
athletes, we COUNT on it. How can we live vicariously through a
bunch of millionaire jocks who behave like _ us? By EJ MONTINI.
Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' category. &QL; 
