<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BROUS-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KC HEAD OF PLANNED PARENTHOOD DIES  
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By SHAWNA A. HAMEL   
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ The longtime president and chief executive
officer of Planned Parenthood of Kansas and Mid-Missouri died
Friday after a battle with cancer.
</P>
<P>
   Planned Parenthood officials recently dedicated the
organization's office as the Patricia Catlin Brous Midtown Center
for Reproductive Services. Brous and her husband, Tom, also
celebrated their 35th wedding anniversary Sept. 12.
</P>
<P>
   Brous, 55, was born in Miami Beach, Fla., but was raised and
spent most of her life in the Kansas City area, said Brous' son,
Joel. She began volunteering for Planned Parenthood in 1974, then
served on its board of directors and became the organization's
development director.
</P>
<P>
   Brous took over as the organization's president and CEO in 1990,
he said.
</P>
<P>
   ``My mom was a huge, huge believer in self-determination, and
what she believed in pervaded her entire life,'' Joel Brous, 28,
said. ``What was really special and her guiding force is that she
respected everyone's personal choices. She really touched people in
all different walks of life, because she was such a hard worker and
so tenacious in making sure people could make informed choices.''
</P>
<P>
   Brous also served as past president of the Junior League of
Kansas City and was on the board of the Historical Kansas City
Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   Brous was diagnosed and treated for breast cancer in 1985.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to her husband and son, she is survived by a
daughter, Anna Catlin Brous, a daughter-in-law, Carrie, her mother,
Dorothy H. Catlin, and siblings, Philancy C. Hedges, Christopher S.
Catlin and Joel O. Catlin, and mother-in-law, Augusta G. Brous.
</P>
<P>
   A celebration of Brous' life will be Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
